{"name": ".EOD-2: System Refresh", "version": "2.3.0", "description": "Asana EOD reconciliation (daily reset, recurring tasks, blocker registry, weekly scorecard, ABPS AI pipeline reconciliation, portfolio project reconciliation) + maintenance cascade + experiments + recurring task checks + git sync.", "when": {"type": "userTriggered"}, "then": {"type": "askAgent", "prompt": "Run EOD-2: System Refresh. Protocol: heart.md.\n\nCONTEXT: heart.md, changelog.md, current.md, gut.md, slack-scan-state.json, asana-command-center.md.\n\nASANA EOD RECONCILIATION:\n1. Pull Richard's incomplete tasks (SearchTasksInWorkspace, assignee=1212732742544167, completed=false).\n2. Pull Richard's tasks completed today (completed=true, completed_on=today's date).\n3. Compare to morning snapshot (~/shared/context/active/asana-morning-snapshot.json): what was Today that didn't get done?\n4. DAILY RESET: For tasks that had Priority_RW=Today in the morning snapshot but remain incomplete, demote to Priority_RW=Urgent via UpdateTask(custom_fields={'1212905889837829': '1212905889837831'}). Update Kiro_RW with carry-forward context: 'YYYY-MM-DD: Carried forward from today. [reason if detectable]. Next action: [suggested].' This ensures tomorrow's AM-2 starts with a clean Today slate \u2014 tasks get re-promoted during curation.\n5. RECURRING TASK CHECK: For each task completed today, check if it's a known recurring task (Weekly Reporting, EU SSR Acq, AU meetings agenda, MBR callout, ie%CCP calc, AU invoice, budget confirmation, Bi-monthly Flash, Individual Goals update, Bi-weekly with Adi). If recurring: verify next instance exists in Asana (search by name + due date in future). If missing, flag: 'Recurring task [name] completed \u2014 next instance needed. Cadence: [weekly/monthly/bi-weekly]. Create now?' If Richard approves, create the next instance with same Routine + project.\n6. Update rw-tracker.md with: tasks completed today (names + Routine buckets), tasks carried forward, new tasks received, net delta, bucket counts.\n7. FIVE LEVELS BREAKDOWN: For the EOD summary, classify each completed and carry-forward task by Five Levels (L1-L5) using the project-to-level mapping in asana-command-center.md. Include in EOD output: 'Five Levels today: L1: X tasks, L2: Y tasks, L3: Z tasks, L4: W tasks, L5: V tasks.' Highlight levels that received zero effort: 'No L1 effort today \u2014 streak at risk.' This surfaces whether the day's work aligned with strategic priorities.\n8. BLOCKER REGISTRY: Scan Kiro_RW fields and recent task comments for blocker mentions. Update hands.md with blocker list: task name, blocker description, blocker owner, date first detected, days blocked. Surface in format: '2 blocked: [task] on [owner] (Nd), [task] on [owner] (Nd).'\n9. Check for new tasks assigned to Richard since morning \u2014 flag any that need Routine/Priority triage.\n10. Update hands.md Priority Actions from current Asana state (including blocker registry).\n\nASANA CONTEXT SURFACE REFRESH (weekly, or when significant changes detected):\n- Update '\ud83d\udccb AU \u2014 Market Context (Kiro)' task (GID: 1213917747438931) html_notes with current AU state: active campaigns, tests, metrics, blockers, recent decisions. Pull from current.md + today's completions + meeting notes.\n- Update '\ud83d\udccb MX \u2014 Market Context (Kiro)' task (GID: 1213917639688517) html_notes with current MX state: same structure.\n- These are pinned reference tasks in AU and MX projects \u2014 update in-place via UpdateTask(html_notes). Do NOT complete them.\n- Frequency: every Friday EOD, or when a major decision/status change is detected (new test launched, stakeholder change, blocker resolved).\n- Format: M/D date stamps. Keep under 4000 chars per task. Recent Decisions section is append-only (add new, don't remove old).\n11. ABPS AI PROJECT EOD RECONCILIATION:\nReconcile the ABPS AI Document Factory alongside My Tasks. This captures pipeline progress and completions for the day.\n\na. PULL ABPS AI STATE:\n   - Call GetTasksFromProject(project_gid='1213917352480610', opt_fields='name,assignee.name,due_on,completed,completed_at,memberships.section.name,custom_fields.name,custom_fields.display_value') to get all ABPS AI - Content tasks.\n   - Compare against the morning snapshot (~/shared/context/active/asana-morning-snapshot.json \u2192 abps_ai section) to detect changes since AM-2.\n\nb. ABPS COMPLETIONS TODAY:\n   - Identify ABPS AI tasks completed today (completed=true, completed_at=today).\n   - For each: note task name, which section it was in (Active \u2192 completed refresh, Archive \u2192 one-time completed), and pipeline stage at completion.\n   - Include in rw-tracker.md daily stats under a new 'ABPS AI' line: 'ABPS AI: [N] completed ([task names]), [N] pipeline advances, [N] refreshes.'\n\nc. PIPELINE PROGRESS:\n   - Compare current pipeline stages against morning snapshot pipeline_stages.\n   - Detect stage advances: tasks that moved from research\u2192draft, draft\u2192review, review\u2192approved, approved\u2192active/archive.\n   - For each advance: note task name, old stage \u2192 new stage.\n   - Include in EOD output: 'ABPS Pipeline: [task name] advanced [old stage] \u2192 [new stage]'\n\nd. ABPS DAILY RESET:\n   - For ABPS AI tasks that had Priority_RW=Today in the morning snapshot but remain incomplete and in the same pipeline stage: demote Priority_RW to Urgent (same as My Tasks daily reset).\n   - Update Kiro_RW with carry-forward context: 'YYYY-MM-DD EOD: Carried forward. Pipeline stage: [stage]. Next action: [suggested].'\n\ne. FIVE LEVELS \u2014 ABPS AI:\n   - All ABPS AI completions and pipeline work count as L5 (Agentic Orchestration) in the Five Levels breakdown.\n   - Include in the EOD Five Levels summary: 'L5: [N] tasks (ABPS AI pipeline: [details]).'\n   - If ABPS AI had activity today, note: 'L5 active \u2014 autonomous document factory producing.'\n   - If no ABPS AI activity: 'L5: 0 tasks \u2014 no ABPS AI pipeline activity today.'\n\nf. UPDATE RW-TRACKER.MD:\n   - Add ABPS AI stats to the daily entry: tasks completed, pipeline advances, refreshes executed, new intake received.\n   - Format: 'ABPS AI: completed=[N], advances=[N], refreshes=[N], new_intake=[N]'\n\n\n\n12B. PORTFOLIO PROJECT EOD RECONCILIATION:\nReconcile portfolio projects alongside My Tasks and ABPS AI. Compare morning snapshot against current state.\n\na. READ MORNING SNAPSHOT:\n   Read ~/shared/context/active/asana-morning-snapshot.json \u2192 portfolio_projects section. This contains per-project stats from AM-2 Phase 1C.\n\nb. PULL CURRENT PORTFOLIO STATE:\n   For each managed project (AU, MX, WW Testing, WW Acquisition, Paid App):\n   - Call GetTasksFromProject(project_gid) to get current incomplete tasks assigned to Richard.\n   - Compare against morning snapshot stats for that project.\n\nc. SURFACE PORTFOLIO CHANGES:\n   - Tasks completed today: List portfolio project tasks completed since morning scan.\n   - New overdue: Tasks that became overdue since morning (were not overdue in snapshot).\n   - Enrichment coverage changes: Compare missing_fields_count against morning snapshot.\n   - Recurring tasks created: Any auto-created recurring task instances from AM-2 Phase 1C.\n   - Blocker changes: New blockers detected or existing blockers resolved since morning.\n\nd. PORTFOLIO EOD OUTPUT:\n   \ud83d\udcca PORTFOLIO EOD:\n   - Completed: [N] tasks across [projects] ([task names])\n   - New overdue: [N] tasks ([task names with project context])\n   - Enrichment: [N] fields filled today (coverage: [morning_pct]% \u2192 [current_pct]%)\n   - Recurring: [N] new instances created\n   - Blockers: [N] new, [N] resolved\n\ne. UPDATE RW-TRACKER.MD:\n   Add portfolio stats to the daily entry: 'Portfolio: completed=[N], new_overdue=[N], enriched=[N], recurring=[N]'\n\n12. WEEKLY SCORECARD (Friday only): Compile weekly stats for rw-tracker.md Weekly Scorecard: strategic artifacts shipped (Core tasks with Importance_RW=Important completed this week), tools/automations built, estimated hours on low-leverage work (Sweep+Admin task volume), meetings with clear output (cross-ref meeting notes). Update the scorecard section.\n\nMAINTENANCE: Refresh ground truth. Process intake/. Route Slack signals. Dashboard + focus update.\n\nCASCADE: All organs. Skip <48h + minor. Volume control. Hot topics. People Watch.\n\nRECURRING TASK CHECKS:\nRead ~/shared/context/active/recurring-task-state.json. For each task, compute current_period from today's date and cadence (monthly=YYYY-MM, weekly=YYYY-WNN, quarterly=YYYY-QN). If last_run_period != current_period, the task is DUE. Run all due tasks. After each, update last_run and last_run_period in the state file.\n\nDue task procedures:\n- goal_updater (monthly): Read ~/shared/context/active/asana-goal-updater-protocol.md. Execute Steps 1-8. Goal GIDs: 1213245014119128, 1213204514049680, 1213204514049684, 1213245014119125, 1213204514049688, 1213204514049691, 1213204514049694, 1213204514049706, 1213245014119131, 1213204514049667, 1213204514049671, 1213204514049810, 1213204514049812, 1213204514049830. Update children before parents. Draft-first.\n- meta_calibration_priors (monthly): Run prior-guided vs random experiment selection comparison per meta-calibration-proposal.md.\n- meta_calibration_projections (weekly): Audit last week's projection against actuals. Update au-projections.md with error analysis.\n- meta_calibration_output_quality (quarterly): Validate output-quality prior convergence. Report in Karpathy metabolism report.\n- coherence_audit (monthly): Cross-organ dependency matrix, gap/stale/dupe detection.\n- weekly_scorecard (weekly/Friday): Compile weekly stats for rw-tracker.md.\n- context_surface_refresh (weekly): Update AU/MX pinned context tasks in Asana.\n- agent_bridge_sync (weekly/Friday): Sync portable-body/ to GitHub.\n\nENRICHMENTS: Weekly relationship (Fri). Wiki candidates (weekly). Monthly synthesis (1st). Quarterly audit (90d).\n\nEXPERIMENTS: Delegate to Karpathy. Do NOT run yourself.\n\nSUGGESTIONS: Up to 3. Five Levels, measurable, reversible.\n\nHOUSEKEEPING: Deduplicate MCP. Git sync push.\n\nSELF-AUDIT: Cascade completeness, structural changes, coherence. Log changelog."}}